HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 629
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend The Harding Art
Show on the occasion of its fiftieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
those longstanding artistic events that enrich the cultural fabric of our State; and
WHEREAS, The Harding Art Show, hosted annually by Harding Academy in Nashville, is
one such estimable event that, since its inception in 1975, has become one of the largest and
most profitable fine art exhibitions in the southeastern United States; and
WHEREAS, on May 1â€“3, 2025, Harding Academy will celebrate the fiftieth anniversary
of The Harding Art Show, marking five decades of commitment to the arts and community
engagement; and
WHEREAS, this highly anticipated annual event showcases over seventy-five talented
artists from around the country, representing various styles across multiple mediums; and
WHEREAS, The Harding Art Show is Harding Academy's single largest fundraising
event, attracting more than 5,000 visitors to the campus over a three-day period, featuring
festive events for attendees aged twenty-one and over, as well as a designated Family Day, all
free to attend; and
WHEREAS, the mission of The Harding Art Show is to build community, share
impeccable and curated art selections, and support Nashville's Harding Academy and arts
education; and
WHEREAS, the fiftieth anniversary show will feature artist Laura McCarty, whose work
embodies the welcoming and joyful spirit of the Harding community; and
